from dataclasses import dataclass

@dataclass
class Triple:
    subject: str
    predicate: str
    object: str

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START

def predict(triples: list[Triple]) -> str:
    if not triples:
        return ""

    sentences = []
    for triple in triples:
        if triple.predicate == "category":
            sentences.append(f"{triple.subject} is a {triple.object}.")
        elif triple.predicate == "country":
            sentences.append(f"{triple.subject} is in {triple.object}.")
        elif triple.predicate == "location":
            sentences.append(f"{triple.subject} is located in {triple.object}.")
        elif triple.predicate == "municipality":
            sentences.append(f"{triple.subject} is in the municipality of {triple.object}.")
        elif triple.predicate == "state":
            sentences.append(f"{triple.subject} is in the state of {triple.object}.")
        elif triple.predicate == "district":
            sentences.append(f"{triple.subject} is in the {triple.object}.")
        elif triple.predicate == "established" or triple.predicate == "foundingDate":
            sentences.append(f"{triple.subject} was established on {triple.object}.")
